  "title": "Engineering Technician | 5 Days | Up to $2800 | 9755",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role: Engineering Technician</strong></p><p><strong>Industry: Engineering</strong></p><p><strong>Location: Nearest Lentor MRT</strong><br /><br /><strong>5 days | Mon-Fri: 8.30am – 6.15pm</strong></p><p><strong>Salary: $2500 - $2800</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Diploma/NITEC or equivalent in a related field.</strong></li><li><strong>Proven experience in a technical or maintenance role.</strong></li><li><strong>Strong mechanical and technical aptitude, with the ability to use a variety of hand and power tools.</strong></li></ol><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Provide direct support to the team leader and engineering staff on daily assignments and projects.</li><li>Prepare and organize tools and equipment for daily tasks and ensure all necessary materials are available and in good working order.</li><li>Perform routine maintenance and calibration on a wide range of tools and equipment to ensure optimal performance and longevity.</li><li>Actively participate in daily housekeeping activities to maintain a clean, safe, and organized workshop and premises. This includes cleaning work areas, storing tools properly, and disposing of waste materials appropriately.</li><li>Assist in troubleshooting and repair of equipment and systems under the guidance of senior technicians or engineers</li><li>Maintain accurate records of equipment maintenance, repairs, and inventory.</li><li>Adhere strictly to all safety protocols and procedures, including the use of personal protective equipment (PPE).</li><li>Collaborate effectively with team members to achieve project goals and maintain a positive work environment.</li></ul><p><br />Tai Jia Seng Reg No: R26159755</p><p>The Supreme Hr Advisory Pte Ltd EA No: 14C7279</p>",
